    "cs_faq_sec_igVimy": {
      "type": "cs_faq_sec",
      "blocks": {
        "best_sellers_mnnnaL": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "How many doses of Wegovy are in a pen?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Each Wegovy FlexTouch pen contains 4 doses. Since Wegovy is injected once per week, one pen usually lasts 4 weeks when used as prescribed.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_inzVJg": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "How much weight can I lose in 1 month with Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Weight loss varies from person to person. During the first month, most people are taking the starting dose (0.25 mg), which is mainly used to help the body adjust to the medication. Because of this, weight loss may be modest at first.</p><p>More noticeable weight loss often occurs after the dose is gradually increased over several months.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_yxYHwe": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Does Wegovy come in an injectable pen?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Yes. Wegovy is supplied as a pre-filled FlexTouch injection pen designed for easy self-administration at home.</p><p>It is injected once weekly under the skin (subcutaneous injection), usually in the:</p><ul><li>Abdomen</li><li>Thigh</li><li>Upper arm</li></ul><p>A <strong>new needle should be used for each injection</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_TUqz7R": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "How much is Wegovy in the UK per month?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>In the UK, Wegovy typically costs around £150–£300 per month, depending on:</p><ul><li>The dose prescribed</li><li>The pharmacy or clinic provider</li><li>Whether consultation or monitoring services are included</li></ul><p>Prices can vary between providers.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_RXK9RA": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Which is better, Mounjaro or Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Both Wegovy and Mounjaro are medications used to support weight loss.</p><ul><li>Wegovy (semaglutide) works by reducing appetite and helping you feel fuller for longer.</li><li>Mounjaro (tirzepatide) works on two hormone pathways involved in appetite and blood sugar regulation.</li></ul><p>Some studies suggest Mounjaro may lead to greater average weight loss, but the best option depends on your medical history and your prescriber’s advice.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_i4hViX": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Can you lose 20 pounds in 2 months on Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Some people may experience significant weight loss, but losing 20 pounds (about 9 kg) in 2 months is not typical for most patients.</p><p>Healthy weight loss with Wegovy is usually gradual and steady, especially when combined with:</p><ul><li>Healthy eating</li><li>Regular physical activity</li><li>Consistent medication use</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_WChzh3": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "What foods should you avoid on Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>To help minimise side effects, try to limit:</p><ul><li>Fatty or fried foods</li><li>Very sugary foods</li><li>Large meals</li><li>Highly processed foods</li><li>Excess alcohol</li></ul><p>Many people find it helpful to focus on:</p><ul><li>Lean protein</li><li>High-fibre foods</li><li>Smaller balanced meals</li><li>Drinking plenty of water</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_AfB4Cz": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "What are the worst side effects of Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Common side effects include:</p><ul><li>Nausea</li><li>Vomiting</li><li>Diarrhoea</li><li>Constipation</li><li>Stomach discomfort</li></ul><p>These symptoms are <strong>usually mild and improve as your body adjusts</strong>.</p><p>Rare but serious side effects can include:</p><ul><li>Pancreatitis</li><li>Gallbladder problems</li><li>Severe abdominal pain</li></ul><p>If symptoms are severe or persistent, <strong>seek medical advice</strong>.<br/><br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_Hckcr6": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Can you drink alcohol while on Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Alcohol can usually be consumed in moderation, but it may:</p><ul><li>Increase nausea or stomach upset</li><li>Reduce weight-loss progress for some people</li></ul><p>Many people find they naturally drink less alcohol while taking Wegovy.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_49PkfM": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Who cannot take Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Wegovy may not be suitable if you:</p><ul><li>Are pregnant or breastfeeding</li><li>Have a personal or family history of medullary thyroid cancer</li><li>Have multiple endocrine neoplasia syndrome type 2 (MEN2)</li><li>Are allergic to semaglutide</li><li>Have certain severe gastrointestinal conditions</li></ul><p>Always speak with a doctor, pharmacist, or prescriber before starting treatment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_pFDenH": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "Why does Wegovy make you not want to drink?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Wegovy can affect the areas of the brain that control appetite and reward, which may reduce cravings not only for food but also for alcohol in some people.</p><p>It also slows stomach emptying, which can make alcoholic drinks feel heavier or less enjoyable. Because of this, some people find they naturally drink less alcohol while taking Wegovy.</p>"
          }
        },
        "best_sellers_zYpLha": {
          "type": "best-sellers",
          "settings": {
            "heading_faq": "What vitamins should I take on Wegovy?",
            "heading_ans": "<p>Wegovy does not usually require routine vitamin supplements.</p><p>However, some people may benefit from:</p><ul><li>A general multivitamin</li><li>Vitamin D (commonly recommended in the UK)</li></ul><p>Always check with a healthcare professional before starting supplements.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
